<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-03T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="1147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1147">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.00/21</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-03T16:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3.40 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4654. Your 3608, August 2, 5 p. m. I delivered to Lord <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Grey</persName> to-day your 3606 which reached me
                            this morning. He did not promise an answer but said he would communicate
                            the Senate’s resolution to the Prime Minister and probably lay it before
                            the Cabinet.</p>
                        <p>Casement was executed early this morning.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>